description: >
  Manage research discipline: hypothesis pre-registration, holdout data,
  preventing strategy degradation. Use when starting new research,
  validating results, or documenting findings.
---

# Research Workflow

## Pre-Registration
Before running any backtest:
1. Document hypothesis in `research/hypotheses/{YYYY-MM-DD}_{name}.md`
2. Specify: signal logic, expected sign, universe, time period
3. Define success criteria before seeing results

## Holdout Protocol
- Training: 2015-2020
- Validation: 2021-2022
- Test (holdout): 2023-2024 (touch ONCE)

## Validation Checklist
- [ ] Hypothesis pre-registered
- [ ] No data snooping on holdout
- [ ] Multiple testing correction applied
- [ ] Out-of-sample Sharpe > 0.5
- [ ] Turnover economically viable
- [ ] Results robust to Â±20% parameter perturbation

## Documentation
After research complete:
1. Update `research/findings/{name}.md`
2. Record: what worked, what didn't, parameter sensitivity
3. If promoting to production, update `src/strategies/`

## References
See [validation-checklist.md](validation-checklist.md) for detailed criteria.
